text: U.S Route 17 is a north-south highway in the Southeastern United States. The highway is close to the East Coast of the United States except the part between Punta Gorda, Florida and Jacksonville, Florida. The southern ending section of the highway is in Punta Gorda, Florida and the northern ending section is in Winchester. The highway spans multiple states which are Florida, Georgia, North Carolina, South Carolina, and Virginia. Category:U.S. Highways
title: U.S. Route 17
